About Me

I am a Cybersecurity, GRC, AI Governance, and IT Project Management consultant with over 25 years of cross-industry experience designing secure infrastructures, enabling digital transformation, and leading complex initiatives across:

Banking & Financial Institutions

Healthcare & Diagnostics

Media Networks

Education Institutes

Logistics, Industrial & Aviation Environments

Telecom & ISP Ecosystems

My work blends deep technical engineering with modern security governance, allowing me to operate comfortably at both strategic and implementation layers.

Over the years, I’ve:

led core banking migrations from mainframe to Oracle

built SIEM/SOC environments using Splunk and Wazuh

implemented enterprise-grade ISO 27001 programs

helped development teams pass security audits and reduce risk exposure

deployed industrial-grade networks, wireless systems, and data centers

enabled multi-branch expansions across countries

supported healthcare organizations in achieving HIPAA-aligned architecture

led telecom, surveillance, and access control projects end-to-end

Today, I specialize in AI Risk Management and AI Governance (ISO/IEC 42001) — helping founders and organizations identify blind spots early and build trust-driven systems.

I also author The Founder’s Risk Mirror, a practical series designed for AI startup leaders navigating governance, security, and compliance with clarity.

My Mission

To help organizations build systems that are secure by design, resilient under pressure, and trusted by customers, regulators, and investors.

What I’m Known For

Strong technical + strategic balance

End-to-end delivery ownership

Clear, calm communication

Ability to simplify complexity

Helping teams and founders “see the risks before anyone else does”
